**5. Point 1: On the Status Quo**
It has been some time. They are still stuck in this small room. Bernard Zie suddenly passes out, collapsing to the ground. (( @Horatius Kyodu ))

Horatius stands there in shock for a few seconds, mouth hanging open, before shaking themself out of their state of shock and rushing over to his collapsed body. "Bern?!" they ask, instinctively trying to feel for a heartbeat.
He's alive. And then he wakes up. #horatius-voreverl
Voreverl Leocot.
((can you elaborate on that))
((why are you the ONLY one online i need a few minutes for you to actually start today))

Voreverl Leocot wakes up in a small room, with a metal door and metal hatch on the ground. In this room are Horatius Kyodu, Wress Hifele, and someone you do not recognize. Most of this final person's body is obscured by their armored clothing, which includes strings running across their torso that form a shape that looks like :wyrdwyrd:. The place where their face would be looks like television static.

#horatius-voreverl
((horatius voreverl))
((round 2?))

Voreverl Leocot looks around frantically for a moment "What!? No! Not right now! Ugghh, can't these things have a warning, or like, a box you check when you're ready!? I hope that fool knows how to drive... Whatever, your glorious leader Voreverl Leocot is back yadda yadda, who the hell is this?" Voreverl points to television static man.
"What is wrong with this youth?" That person asks this.

"Wh-" Horatius is momentarily caught off guard before their face falls, slapping their palm against their forehead. "Ugh… I guess this is what we're doing now, huh? This is our other friend Voreverl. She's, uh… another inhabitant of this body, for the time being. Don't spend too much time thinking about it."
"...I see. Never mind. I am Wyrd." Wyrd speaks with a voice resembling an adult woman :fornote:

"Well, 'Wyrd', your costume seems to be glitching out a bit, might want to get that fixed. Anyway, you guys can drop the act now. I was really fired up about this whole revolution thing before, but now that I know it's all fake, I can't say I care. It's not really evil to conquer a fake world."
"The- Sorry, the *what?* I assure you, we're not 'acting' out anything. If you know something about this world that we don't, you'll have to be the one to tell it to us. With proof, preferably."
"This person is very obviously suffering from delusions of some kind. It does not matter." Wyrd moves closer to the door, examining it.
"Yeah… she's like this sometimes. Sorry about that."

"Gweheheh, are you telling me... Oh, that'd be too good if you guys don't know. John's outdone himself here, I'll have to work overtime to prove myself eviler than he. Whatever, it doesn't really matter if you're lying or not. Not like I have anything better to do while I'm here."
"Prove yourself.... evil?" Wyrd turns back.

"Of course, spending my time proving anything else would be a waste of effort! I'm the cruelest, evilest, most dangerous villain of all time! And it's an unforgivable failure on your part that you haven't already heard of me. This world is so incompetent, really."
"Look, whatever all that means, are you still on our revolution's side here, or are you not?" they ask with a sigh.
"I see. I will prioritize killing you after this, then." Wyrd turns back to the door.

"Uhh... hm." Voreverl looks deep in thought "Gweheheh, I suppose it will work as a test run. A training simulation for the real deal! As long as you keep this faceless fool on a leash, that is. Threatening someone as grand as I, really, what kind of idiot are you?"

"Works for me." Horatius shrugs. "Either way, don't expect to see Wyrd working alongside us again. He's been trying to kill us this entire time; we're just taking a break for the time being. As soon as we get out of this building, we're going right back to being enemies."
"Unfortunately, I have made a vow of non-aggression while we remain here, and remain here we must."
Wress finally fucking talks. "Furn's been locked away in some room around here."

"Gwehohoh... I see, so that's how it is. You guys are feigning a truce to betray this idiot while their back is turned, aren't you? You've already learned so much from me, I'm proud of your growth. That's what they get for not realizing that evil never sleeps!" Voreverl definitely says this at a volume where everyone present can hear it.
"It is obvious we will stop being in alignment immediately after this. There is a fundamental ideological schism." Wyrd explains, annoyed.

They nod in mock satisfaction. "Yes, exactly. In fact, we were even thinking how wonderfully that plan was going to work as long as we didn't announce it straight to his face. Unfortunately, we'll have to think of something else now."

"You really don't have backup plans already? I guess I have to do *everything* around here. No, no, it's not a problem at all, just an evil mastermind's job to always have contingency plans. You'll learn the skill with time."
"Of course, why didn't we think of that… Your genius strikes again."

"Are you unable to take responsibility for your own missteps? Then you are a failure as a leader." Wyrd.

"I mean, technically, she's not..." Wress mumbles out, doing the Ron DeLite text thing.

"Villains don't take 'responsibility'. I can't believe I have to explain this, it's really the simplest thing. Why do you think I have these minions? It's to throw them in front of me like meat shields when the going gets tough."
Horatius turns away and pointedly looks anywhere but at Voreverl.

"Of course. You in particular are much more akin to him than to the somewhat respectable Hifele patriarch. May you rot."

Someone unlocks the door from the outside. "Hey, what's going on here?!"
"Oh? Has another worthless minion arrived to get us out of this embarrassingly dull cell? I suppose the fun can begin, then." Voreverl moves towards the door.
Horatius spins around. "Voreverl, come back here now. We're still trying to figure out how to break Furn free. Don't you want to have more minions on your side?"

"Well, he's certainly a useful minion, and loyal too... Gweheheh, which would make leaving him behind all the more evil, don't you think? Just imagine the look on his face when he realizes he was left behind by the body of his best friend. Oh, I haven't done a proper betrayal in a while!"
The man at the door raises a weapon, and Wyrd kicks him in the face. "We can move now."

"Wh- You- He- Th-" they sputter. "No. You know what? I can't take this shit anymore. All your idealism has ever done is fuck us over whenever we're trying to do *anything*, and all you do is cling to it like it's the most important thing in the world, something that you have to follow above all else, when all you've really been following is yourself. And you can't even do anything right on your own, you fucking moron. You think you were following us around this whole time because *you* were leading *us*? You think we needed someone to make things harder for us at every possible turn just because we were so devoted to your leadership? We were leading *you* this entire time, asshole, because we thought *maybe* you could be of use here, but now I see that it might be more useful to have to drag around your unconscious body until whoever it is that's doing this lets you leave again. I should have never even pretended to be friends with someone with such an ass-backwards ideology that just gets in the way of even the simplest fucking things! Fuck!" They put their head in their hands.
They take their head out of their hands and attempt to punch Voreverl in the face with maximum force.
((roll to. hit?????))
((Roll what))
((a d20 (it's an attack) ))
((Unarmed strike is with strength and proficiency modifier))
((Oh okay uh))
((That would be 10 then))
((I am not hit 🥳))

Voreverl recoils back "You... You tried to knock me out!? Your leader!? What is wrong with you! I know I complimented your betrayal plan, but this is no way to demonstrate growth! Respecting your leader comes above all else! No... I don't even want you as a minion! In fact, this just proves how evil I am! Able to drive away even the most devoted of followers because you just can't stand how morally impure I am, that's what this is about isn't it!? Well *thank you* for the compliment! Now, if you don't mind, not that I'd care if you did, I'll be taking this idiot's body and conquering this world on my own!"
Wyrd has already left. Wress gets up. "Hey, calm down... You two can fight about this when we're able to get out of this mess, okay? Just keep it together a little longer. Please."

"Wress, she doesn't *care*. If we stopped now, she'd just screw off to who-knows-where and leave us all behind. And even if we didn't do this now, she'd *still* probably ditch us at some point anyways! Did you even hear what she was saying before?! She wanted to use us as *meat shields!* I've had to compromise for her so many damn times, and if I have to do it again, she's just going to take advantage of it! Our best course of action right now is to make sure she doesn't fuck anything else up. Are you going to help me or not?!"
((When will it be my turn again I wish to strangle her))
((if we're going to do a real combat then initiative rolls))
Voreverl Leocot is first.

"Horatius, what does this matter? You've always been annoyed at me for the distinction between saying ideals and actually putting them into practice! Voreverl has from the start said she's going to do a bunch of different evil things, some of which contradict each other! It only matters what she actually *does*!"
Wress, of course.

Voreverl looks really proud of herself "So you figured me out then... You finally get it! Horatius has read me like a book! I would take any opportunity I could to screw the rest of you over! That's what a villain does! Tsk, tsk, and I almost thought that I'd get to see you buffoons writhe in confusion once I got around to betraying you, such a shame that it was not meant to be!" Voreverl is going to use the disengage action and using cunning action she can also use the dash action. She is running out the door with a movement speed of 60.
That is her turn.
Horatius gestures to Voreverl doing this while mouthing "see?" at Wress and raising their eyebrows.
Wress uses his turn to follow after her. "Ugh! It doesn't matter! I'm finding Furn!" Horatius chooses now what to do.
Horatius also chooses to follow after Voreverl Leocot from Voreverl Leocot.
ACTUALLY can they take like one second to type something on their PDA and then follow after Voreverl Leocot
sure lmao
Okay they did it and are now running after VL from TAP
It's insane how much running is being done.

They manage to meet up with Wyrd, who is fending off like five or so random guards. "It should be past that staircase."

The staircase is blocked. It is again the turn of @Natyobb.
I'm removing the ambiguity it's EXACTLY five.

"Gweheheh, so these guards are enemies of yours, then? I suppose they will make sufficient replacement minions in lieu of my revolutionaries! Guards, execute these fools!" Voreverl uses the dodge action and ends her turn.
Okay. Wress groans in anguish and stabs one of the guards, muttering something about non-violent protest. @Horatius Kyodu turn.
((Can I ignore the guards and attack Voreverl or do I HAVE to fight them))

Horatius Kyodu ignores the guards and attempts to strangle Voreverl, finally allowing their dynamic to come full circle.

Voreverl is??? Being strangled??? ((I have no idea if I'm aware what's going on here but sure that sounds right))

Wyrd stares back at this tomfoolery and then shoves guards out of the way to run up the stairs.

It is Voreverl Leocot's turn again.
Voreverl Leocot tries in vain to sputter something out and then attempts to free herself. ((7))
((Horatius rolls strength again))

Horatius continues to strangle Voreverl, starting to laugh as they do it. "You know, you should feel lucky that out of all the bodies you ended up in, it just happened to be the one I love the most. I probably would have killed you already if I didn't care so much about him!" ((12)) They are very normal
Oh yeah that was Voreverl's entire turn for note I don't think I can do anything else lol.
Wress tries to wrest off Horatius, initiating another roll for a grapple contest.
This is a fucking 4.
It still works. "We still need the body, if nothing else!"
The guards, who seem to have remembered to exist, finally act after coming to their senses from whatever the fuck that was.
One stabs Voreverl for 10 damage. The rest miss. Back to @Natyobb.
Voreverl uses uncanny dodge to halve the damage she takes because she can do that.
((USES *WHAT* DODGE))

Voreverl reaches for her neck and starts taking in breaths again. She glares at Horatius "Wh-What the hell is wrong with you!? This is the second time you... Ugh! Why can't you just let me commit evil without you getting in my way!? You know what, I don't care, don't answer that! I couldn't give a shit about whatever failure of a thought train led to that track of incoherence! Just leave me alone!" Voreverl disengages and dashes up the stairs, assuming she can get past the guards.
This works.
Though guards chase after her.
"Horatius, wait." Wress says this. ((Back to separate channels.))
It's the following morning. MBMJ wakes up in the place he went to sleep. (( @Mr. Big Man III ))
((i just remembered this is the week you specifically said I Can't Make It lol. regardless its fine yeah))
**MBMJ springs awake.** "Gah-hah!" **He looks around.** "Ah yes, I had my bout today!" **He jumps in the air and then bolts to the arena, the place of his bout.**
He arrives there. Docker is in the. Fucking room where you get ready or whatever. "G'morning, lad. Need a refresher on anything? Should just be a simple match, the outcome can really go either way."

**He nods at Docker.** "But of course! How I've longed for the stage... I've been developing material for this exciting moment on stage!" He casts Enhance Ability on himself, giving himself Bull's Strength. "Have you heard anything from Bruna recently, by the way?"
"Bruna? The lass left a few notes on events in the near future just in case, but she hasn't sent word of any kind, nah."
**MBMJ nods and casts Sending, attempting to contact Bruna.**

Sending a message of:
"Hello Bruna! Hope you are doing well. Reacsian fight today. If you need anything I could help. Enjoy your journey!"
(she can reply immediately if she receives the message, 25 words or less)

He receives a response.
*"Doing alright. At capital. First lead was a bust but I have plenty more to check. Good luck in the ring."*
It is in fact about time for the beginning of the match.
**He nods, grinning, before looking at Docker.** "Ha-ha! Well, I better get going!"
He casts Longstrider on himself before going out on stage.
What's the crowd like?
Definitely not as packed as the rumble the other day, but there's a good bunch of full rows of seats. 50% capacity
They cheer at the entrance of Mr Big Man Jr..

**MBMJ comes out flexing, laughing, pointing to regulars in the audience.**

"Well, looks like the wonderful people of the AWF have only gotten prettier since my last appearance! They say that love is blind, but anyone who says that must not have ever been hearing, watching the wonderful people in the audience reach out with your hearts and voices!" 

Is Cent Ageny here?
((perception roll))
Yeah. He’s looking down right now, but he’s seated in the audience.
Awesome. **MBMJ continues flexing and showing off. Has Reacsian arrived?**
Reacsian emerges from the shadows, staring at MBMJ. His expression is indecipherable. He makes no attempt to attack or speak. He’s more one to react to what his opponent does.
**MBMJ laughs.** "Well, my illustrious opponent arrives! Ser Reacsian, I'm going to come up on you and cock your clock off- and when you think of this day, you'll think "Tuck my life!"
“Typical liberal empty promises.” The word ‘liberal’, for note, holds zero political connotations in Arctica. It is a signature move of Lifetuck to use words strangely like this.

**MBMJ will outstretch his arm.**

"That's the difference between you and I, Mr. Reacsian. I'm not the kinda guy to sit back. To react. Retract. Instead I'll a-ttack. Give back. You're wack. I'm cracked. Laid-back." **MBMJ uses the American custom that some rappers seem to be incorporating: freestyle rapping.**

He will then rush towards Lifetuck. Is Lifetuck within his movement speed? (He has +10 feet because of longstrider)
Yeah.

Epic. So this is the action MBMJ will take.

1. Move action: MBMJ will move to Lifetuck.
2. Standard action: MBMJ will initiate a grapple. Advantage from enhance ability, he rolls 25, 29, keeps 29.
3. As a reaction (heh) to Lifetuck resisting the grapple, MBMJ will use his reaction to use Cutting Words against him.
"Lean back. Quack Quack. I'm a duck. With a shark. You just suck. My remark." This subtracts 1d6 from his roll to not be grappled, which in this case is 1.
4. After attempting to grapple Lifetuck, MBMJ will attempt to shove him prone using his bonus action. He rolls 25, 25, keeps 25.
I've created the most toxic character possible.
you might not believe it but next level I become like. way worse

Lifetuck is overwhelmingly grappled. The cutting words only serve to add insult to injury.

He attempts to dodge the shove but fails so hard that he falls down himself before you even make contact.
Is this the end of MBMJ turn. Have I interpreted this sequence correctly.
Yes
Lifetuck stands up. He then attempts to grapple YOU, because wrestling is very exciting. (17 for his roll here)
MBMJ rolls 19, 20, keeps 20
My turn?

Lifetuck also attempts to use Cutting Words, saying "Well, imagine my shock.", but enunciated such that *shock* sounds like *shark*, a reference to Gamergate. This doesn't really qualify as an insult whatsoever, and it fails to change the outcome. MBMJ's turn.
"...Lifetuck, I could end this right here and pin you... but that would be too boring. I'd like for the two of us to play a game."
"A game, Mebmej? What are you talking about?" Even on the brink of defeat, Lifetuck still remains with a stoic unfocused gaze, pretending he can't even understand what nonsense you're doing.
"Lifetuck... did you have any dreams last night?"
"Perhaps. What of it?"
"Tell me about them!"

"Hmph. I suppose I can play along." He crosses his arms. "I found myself in a frigid wasteland; similar to what I imagine the far north is like. I met a woman, and somehow, I knew that it was the author of Tucker's Reaction, my favorite work of literature. She hit me in the head, and before I could retaliate or ask why, she was gone. I carry this knowledge with me, the same as I will carry my self to the finish line in this battle." He poses confidently. The crowd murmurs; Lifetuck doesn't have nearly your mass appeal, but he has his devotees.

"...Then perhaps that dream will carry you somewhere, Lifetuck. But it won't carry you to the victory. I'm afraid you've ended up without any lifelines, and I'm the one rolling you right back into the station."

MBMJ rolls to pin. He rolls 30, 30, keeps 30.

The pin succeeds. "Ghrk!"

Lifetuck stops resisting. "You win this time... this ring has no place left for my beautiful self. Only frumpy, unsexy M&Ms (misters and mans) shall remain."
**MBMJ smirks, and looks up to the audience. He tries to gauge Ageny's reaction.**
Ageny is getting up to leave.
**MBMJ nods to himself and looks out at the rest of the audience.**
"I bring justice to you Burdlt!"
The crowd does the thing used to express approval, also known as a cheer.
**MBMJ grins and walks away.**
Does he have any more responsibilities before Alfred moment?
Not particularly, no. It's not like SO CLOSE he has to RUSH to make it but yknow its soon after
Sounds good. He'll pull his phone out in the lounge or whatever and text on his PDA, waving his legs back and forth

**MBMJ will use his second sending charge to talk to Baby Crippler.**

*'Are you planning a government insurrection? That would be bad. You know I've gotta uphold justice. Is there an explanation for this?'*
There is no response.
**MBMJ attempts to find the nearest member of wrestling staff who might personally know Baby Crippler.**
Fucking. Let's say it's Docker Powell sure
"Hey Docker... do you have any idea where Baby Crippler is?"

"Nae. His departure was far more abrupt an' unusual than Bruna's. He set out to the southeast last I saw, but I've nary a clue for what. I do keep coming back to it. I know the boy like 'es me own son, surely I can understand this? But I..." He shakes his head. "...Nothing. No answer."

"...A mutual friend I've made has reached out to ask me about him. Apparently, he's been caught up in something bad.

If you hear something, reach out, okay? He was a blood brother to me."

"I see. He's been hot-blooded from the start; I advised 'im to make 'is stage persona mysterious and aloof specifically to counter that. So I'm sad t'say I can very much see BC doing something rash or flat-out dumb. I'll keep my eyes out. Thanks for letting me know, Biggie." ((The true goal of MBMJ route is to determine how many different nicknames I can create for the clunkiest name in existence))
**MBMJ nods at Docker and the heads to the Alfred Moment.**

The Alfred Moment is in a building the interior of which looks sort of like a hospital room. The titular Alfred waves as you enter. "Hey! How've you been, man?" There is also a non-Alfred guy here; a man shrouded in robes that leave only his face exposed. He rolls his eyes when you come in.

"I've been great! A ton has happened, heart of hearts. I hope you've been doing well. I've got something you'd love to look at next time you get a moment." **MBMJ shows Alfred the PDA.** "If you're interested in it, you could give me some insight on it!"

**His gaze turns to the man in the robes.** "Is this our customer today?"

Alfred laughs meekly. “Uh, not quite. This is my boss, S-“

“Solnit.” The robed man interrupts. “I already know your name.” He idly flicks some switches and etches occult patterns onto the wall, a completely benign thing to do since magic is real.
"Hello Solnit! I hope that you are having a righteously just day today!"

“Still like this outside the ring, then?” Solnit mutters.

“Being an actor doesn’t make someone not genuine, you know.” Alfred retorts.

“Whatever. How much has he told you about this project already?”
"I've been told I am to enter someone's dreams using state-of-the-art techniques developed by the finest scholar in all of Burdlt!"
**He beams with pride.**

“Yes, I suppose he is owed a fair bit of credit for this…” Solnit halfheartedly replies.

“I explained the general idea a few days ago.” Alfred.

“In layman’s terms, no doubt. Hm…” Solnit glances around.

"...I know that this technology is meant to be used intimately, by someone you would already trust inside your head: people whose fates are wrapped together with ribbon and twine- in this case, it would generally be used by laypeople... perhaps I am a good specimen in that case?"

“In truth, the ‘client’ would ideally be the technically knowledgeable one. But we will make do.” Solnit directs Alfred to lie down on a bed.

“During development, I was struck with the image of the archaic god of dreams, Somnius. Have you heard of him, Jr?” It is Solnit saying this.
"Somnius? I can't say I've heard of him. What did this sudden inspiration lead you to?" **MBMJ raises at eyebrow at Solnit.**

“The name of this project, which I doubt you’re aware of, since I only finalized it yesterday. For accessing the realms of Somnius as easily as one would files from a folder, no other name seemed more fitting.”

He swishes his robe around with a flourish.

“ZTD! Somnic Terrain Dive. Using the alternate spelling for the deity, since there were some foreseen legal hangups over STD.”

He clears his throat, returning to being serious and stoic. “It will be necessary to be able to speak of ZTD in shorthand for us to cooperate effectively. So I thought I’d let you know now.”
"But of course. Once I begin ZTD, will I know where I am, or will some unknown force tamper with my memory of where I am?"
((i PROMISE this plot thread exists for a reason that isn’t jokes please look forward to seeing it in chapter 80))
(this is awesome)
((ZTD ||"once I begin, will I be mind hacked"||))

“No. …At least, I don’t believe so. That could only result from some unprecedented interaction between minds and souls. If you focus, you should be able to move your body in here outside of the area of effect, so just do that if something feels off in a way that affects your mental state. But!” He raises a finger. “This is not some state than can be hopped in and out of. Until we fix the engineering problem, you have to be in long enough for your existence to restabilize before exiting. You need to stay in ZTD for at least six minutes. Understand?”
"I understand." **His brow furrows.** "There wouldn't happen to be any malignant side effect if I was to exit prematurely, would there be?"

“Again, none of this has ever existed outside of theory before now. Six minutes isn’t a hard limit, just what we’ve judged as definitively safe. You could be fine coming out after five or even four. But the earlier it is, the higher the risk of a catastrophic failure. Insanity. Memory loss. Identity dissolution. A kickback pushing your soul even further out, leaving your body unoccupied forever. And also, death. Those last two are debatably the same thing. That’s for philosophers to whine about.”

**MBMJ nods.** "Understood." **He chuckles, breaking the tension.** "I'm glad I asked about that before! If I had gone into this process unaware of the consequences of failing to take caution of such a weighty condition, I would be a fool indeed!"
**He glances at Alfred.** "...Have your spirits settled about this procedure?"

He smirks. “Hey, I’ve got the easy part.”

Solnit continues. “I’m going to sedate Alfred — the host — now.”
Solnit waves his hands over Alfred’s head without waiting or asking anything, and he conks out instantly.
“This accomplishes the dual purpose of skipping the wait for someone to become unconscious as well as decreasing the likelihood of an unpleasant or hostile environment. Alfred was already deemed mild-mannered enough to be lower risk, but this is another precaution.”
**MBMJ nods at Solnit.** "...Okay, so what do I do? Where do I put my feet?"

“Stand within the white circle.” He points to the ground.

He walks over to a piece of machinery. “When I pull this switch on the console, the safety locks will disengage, and you will begin ZTD. Alfred, of course, will have no way to help or affect anything. Not in any traditional sense. I will be capable of two way communication with you, but this cannot be fully relied on. The passage of time will not necessarily be the same here and there, which could render dialogue incomprehensible. Nevertheless, speaking with the intent to have me hear it should allow you to do just that.”

He takes a deep breath. “I’m not one for idle conversation. Let me know when you are ready.”
**MBMJ goes to the circle.** "So my feet are good here? My feet are like. I can just stand? There's no stand where I put my feet?"
“Yeah. You’re good there.”
"Okay. So I'm just gonna stand, then."
(( MBMJ when time passes significantly faster for him, rendering the exterior communication impossible to respond to https://youtu.be/F0yM97gsjLM ))

messages.content: “Okay.” Okay.
"...I'm sorry, are you sure that there isn't a place to put my feet?"

Solnit groans, leaving the room. He comes back half a minute later with a folding chair, placing it next to the bed.

“.!” He gestures to it impatiently with his hands.
**MBMJ grins.** "I've already passed the first challenge!" **He puts his feet on the chair and gives a thumbs-up to Solnit.**
"Alright. Let's do it!"
(are we doing this today or next week btw)
((next week would be better but im not imminently needing to stop))
okay let's do next week :salute:

((le epic cliffhanger though))
Solnit counts down.
“Five.”
The room is silent.
“Four.” 
Alfred’s body emanates a faint aura.
“Three.”
The circle lights up.
“Two…”
Solnit flicks the switch. The world warps.
…
MBMJ finds himself in a field of wheat. The crop extends seemingly infinitely in all directions. In the near distance (the kind of distance that is near rather than just distant), a building is visible. It’s vaguely familiar.

MBMJ is in the dream.

Solnit's voice can be heard; a little more nervous than before, but otherwise normal. "BM, can you hear me?"
**MBMJ speaks out.** "Loud and clear, little miss voice in the sky. Assuage your worries, king. Your strongest soldier is winning as the lion sleeps tonight."
"In the sky, huh? I like that. Anyway, there should be a concentrated point of interest within a larger space of less detail. You should seek that out."
"...Loud and clear. That's the plan, big man." **MBMJ wavers as he pauses for a moment, before he anxiously walks to the building.**
The geometry is warped somewhat, but this is Wellington House.

Zita "The number is the other falsehood. I have birthed four children. Catarina was a twin. The other child, Bruce, did not survive infancy. This one is less important, but could still result in scandal. That is all I wish to tell you. ...Thank you for your time."

"Yes, thanks... Joliene, stay here, I have a few more things to talk to you about."

Zita turns back. "With my absence necessary?"

Dextrum stares her down. "You should know not to push this."

She huffs in annoyance and leaves the room in a rush.

Dextrum grins sheepishly. "Her majesty can be very intimidating when she desires."

She purses her lips, and nods in a way vaguely sympathetic, but more obviously uncomfortable. She is currently wondering what could have possibly prompted this.

"...I wouldn't call that intimidating, personally."

"I do understand her feelings. I don't intend to be a monster. But it's for everyone's safety that I have to expose more of her lies. And my own I suppose. Hoho."

He turns to you with a more serious expression. "That's not the full story of Bruce. Through nothing short of a miracle, he was returned to this world quite a few years later. In 909. But he died again in less than two years. The existence of this family member was an incredibly well kept secret. But some of the older staff still know. And it's better you hear from someone loyal to the crown than a more dubious source."
"I'm not telling you all this info for no reason. Have you heard of, uh, 'TGP'?"
She blinks, and obviously shifts in her seat. "...Why do you ask?"

He chuckles, and pulls out from the drawers a mask that looks like MBMJ's. 
"Well, it's because that's me. I'm him."

"Huh." Her reaction isn't the most colourful, but her eyes are wider than ever. "Well, uh- hm. I see. Interesting. Yes, very intere... yes. I'll let you explain how this relates to Bruce, but after that, I hope you don't mind if I ask a few questions."

He lets out a deep sigh. "Yes, I'll indulge that in the spirit of cooperation. Bruce was... a pupil of mine, while he walked this land. We interacted often. He was bright. When he died, it was through the same means he arrived in this world. Through that pocket space I've already rambled to you about."

"...I knew it had something to do with that." She grinned. She had a lot of vague suspicions that pointed in contradictory directions, and this was one of them. "This Bruce... he aged inside this pocket space, did he? How does that work?"

"You look awful excited. This is in some sense my biggest failing in life, you know. But I suppose I've been paid back for it now." He looks over at the door containing the space. "It's unusual and inconsistent. On average, time passes faster in there. But there's no real rule. He did spend time in there, yes."
"...Do I need to ask how this relates to The Antarctica Project? I feel like the conclusion from here is clear. Perhaps not the motive, but the method. Some aspect of it, anyway."

"It doesn't, actually. It's not supposed to. I still feel uneasy spilling all the beans, but I'll say that the reason The Antarctica Project was initiated had absolutely nothing to do with Bruce Praxis. Instead, I'm worried if it'll relate to the reason it ends."
"...Elaborate."
Lots of ellipsis. Joliene be thinking.

"Well--I guess I'm more worried if it'll be *not*-- if, uh, he won't be the thing that could end it. Or even if he would that would be concerning, but what I mean is..."
He pauses. "The issue. The chrysalis exiting the space in between. What I talked to you about before. If Bruce wasn't destroyed and killed entirely, he'd have gone to the other end, in that constructed space. But if he had, he would surely have tried to make contact or return. The only reasonable possibility where he's alive... probably... would be from that Gateway. Like he got stuck in the middle and he's found a way to exit." 
He sighs and looks down.
"Basically anything coming out of there should be kill on sight. It's already growing exponentially in this larval state, and it will only become more powerful over time once it emerges. But if it's somehow Bruce... that wouldn't be right to shoot him down when he's coming home."
He stares at you. "The reason I'm telling you about this, the reason it's related to The Antarctica Project, the reason I had to tell you about TGP... is because this closed space has a name. It was called Antarctica as a whole, but the center of it all, the area with simulated life... was dubbed, well, Earth."

Joliene's hand is somewhere between her jaw and lips as she absorbs all this, awed. "So- so there are *more* of these, well- these false worlds. Is that what you're saying? And Earth is the only one that contains life? So... so this would mean he... *circumvented* the path between each, and somehow... sorry, really. This is just a lot to take in." If her legs could function, she'd obviously be standing right now. The antsy way her body shifted made this clear. "And he has a chance to end this all, somehow?"

"Earth is... unique. Within the closed space, all the other worlds are nothing more than decor. And there really is nothing like it in terms of other 'false worlds'. Feels a bit mean to use the term, but I get it. It's the product of generations of work, finalized recently."

"I apologize for my phrasing, then. I'm just... well, I'm not sure what to think of the world itself. It feels lesser, in a lot of ways. Races being homogenous feels like a strict downgrade. At the same time..." She gestures obviously towards her legs.

"Yes, fiction always exists only as a subset of reality. But there is obviously value to this kind of construction. The original purpose was to simulate political situations, for his majesty to make decisions in wartime and policy for the good of the people."
"Of course. I don't mean to imply I don't find value in such simulations either. Really, I'm grateful I was chosen." She pauses. "So what is its purpose now?"

“Hard to say. It still has that kind of research value. But you probably have a sense of how bizarre and massive the scope of this is. Putting you in there is one thing, but you’ve got something like bringing that Richard fellow here as another thing.”

"I'm... sorry if that was a mistake. Forcing him to involve himself in something not just greater than himself, but greater than he was ever designed for..." She hums lowly. "So if the world's continued existence has fuzzy value at best, then what is the Project?"

“What indeed. It really is just an experiment, in part. To see how people react to this. There’s a lot of people, both here and in there, who want this truth to be made public, and it would be good to make sure that won’t lead to… problems.”

"...Then it's politics." She nods quickly. "A few more questions, then, if you don't mind. First of all: what made you select the participants you did from Earth? Second, who is PH and why does the project need several people at the helm? And... er, finally, what can I do to help from here?"

“I didn’t select the participants from Earth. That was PH. The ones from Arctica were my selection. As for PH himself, it was just deemed useful for the project to have major conspirators on both ends, since transport can be finnicky. As for help… well, keep an eye out for any sign of or information on Bruce. Oh, Detlef too, though he’s not nearly as much a mystery. The secret project he’s involved in had him go to earth, and he’s not back when he should be or responding to any of our contact attempts.”
"I see. I'll be sure to keep that in mind, then. Um... thanks again. For trusting me with this knowledge, I mean. It helps a lot. Really."
“It’s not a real risk on my part. Don’t think it’s the kindness of my heart that chose you as a co-conspirator.”
"Well, don't... don't put it like that. I just wanted to voice that this means more to me than you could ever realize. If that's too personal for this meeting, I apologize."
"...I'll be on my way."
“Hmph.” He seems peeved, somehow, as Joliene leaves.
Joliene wheels back to her room. It's probably about time to sleep.

Horatius doesn't look up. They've been looking at their PDA for the past… while, and their awareness of the world around them seems tenuous at best.
“Fuck! You’re shitting me!” Wress uncharacteristically yells. “We… gah! Furn, what the hell?!”

He slumps against a wall. “…What about you, Horatius? Now would be the time to leave if you want. It probably wouldn’t even register on how awful this day already is.”

He’s quiet for a moment, and then shakes his head. “No, that’s harsh. I need y-… need everyone I can get. No man works alone. There should still be some people to recuperate with…”

“Horatius!” He addresses you directly. “I’m sorry, I— I don’t know what that thing is, but is it really more important than this!?” He’s been muttering to himself for several minutes. “If they have any sense, our remaining allies should’ve fled to the planned next destination. We have to go. Maybe we’ll be lucky and those two did the same for some reason.”

"Y-Yeah. Sorry, I just…" They sigh. "Sometimes I feel like I don't even know why I'm doing anything, you know? I guess I… I mean, I don't want to make things harder for you, and I don't want to spring this on you when we're already in the middle of trying to deal with whatever's going on here. But it's just, why are *you* still going, Wress? What is it that makes you want to keep pushing onwards, even in the face of every new terrible day?"

"It's..." He stops to think. "I guess I consider my life a microcosm of everything. Like, I've always centered my political beliefs on the brutal honesty of one phrase. 'A better world is possible, but it's going to have to get worse first.' I mean, we agree that the government is terrible. But the period during and after dealing with that is going to be a lot of people losing their jobs, a lot of poverty, a lot of death." 
Wress sighs, and finally stands up straight.
"It won't stop me, but I think holding on to this knowledge instead of hiding it allows me to stay, um, sane. And grounded. And it's... it's the same with life, isn't it? If you're too focused on immediate short-term comfort, nothing's ever gonna change. From something as simple as getting out of bed in the morning to working on the process to enter a better life."

He tries to look Horatius in the eyes, but falters, and keeps glancing around.

"I need to be the leader. I don't know if I'm the best fit for it, but there's no one that has more potential for uniting people than me. So I act the part as much as I can. I need everyone to feel confident under the assumption they're headed by someone who is confident. I know I don't... I don't do the best job at this. But I think I can come across as someone a little scattered that still has full commitment to his ideals. You... you aren't just my comrade, Horatius. I think of you as a friend. So I'll let you know the truth. Maybe it will help one of us."

Wress tears up a little, and wipes his eyes with his sleeve.

"I'm really scared. I don't want to do this! I want to go back to the encampment and barricade my door and hide in there and cover my ears until people stop trying to contact me. I want dad to handle all of this stuff again. I want mom to come back. You know, the thing- the, what's really fucking sickening? When I was led into the prison, when it seemed there wouldn't actually be any way out, before I contacted your group? I was happy. *Thank god*, I thought. I can be the hero who tried his best, and it would be over now, and I'd be alive. I want things to be better without getting worse."

Wress looks in the direction of the exit. "But that's not possible. None of it is, and I can't forgive the me who indulges in delusion."

"…Well, I'm glad you consider me a friend throughout all of this." Horatius attempts to smile, but their face probably displays pretty clearly that Wress's answer wasn't what they were looking for. It's obvious that this whole thing is scary, but wanting to run away from it all would just be irrational… They've never had a place they could hide away in and not worry about things. So was that it, then? Were they just supposed to see this revolution through for the sake of it? Maybe thinking otherwise was just being selfish, but…
They thought back to the conversation they'd had on their PDA. The situation wasn't exactly the same, but nonetheless, was it really okay for them to pour their life into this without it even being 'a life worth ruining'?
"I'll, uh, see to it that you don't die as best as I can, at least," they manage to reply to Wress.
"Y-yeah." Wress shuffles out of the building uncomfortably.
They follow him immediately, with no time having passed since that exchange at all.

It’s amazing how efficient they’re being. On to Intuitia.

There's what remains of the group hanging around Intuitia, a small area the size of a dog park that may or may not literally be a dog park. Wress looks happier than Horatius has maybe ever seen him before upon discovering this. But Intuition isn't there. Nobody is. There are talks of breaking in to access the resources available to Intuition, but they conclude with the decision that this isn't worth it.

After more walking, though a shorter period, they all arrive at the snow covered city of Elvith. Wress knocks on the door of a tower that stands above the rest of the village. The woman you'd recognize from the funny hologram, Neko, opens.

"Welcome. Are you well? I can't reasonably have room for this entire squadron, but please, at least you and your friend make yourselves at home."

Wress nods, signaling for the others to stay and stand watch outside, while giving a knowing glance at you as he enters the building.

*Hi, Wress. You're probably going to be the first person to find this, so I'm addressing you first. But also- Hi, Bern, Furn, anyone else reading. I don't think this is the situation any of us wanted to find me in, least of all myself. It's sad, but there's no way out of it. And I think I at least owe you an explanation for why it happened.*
*My real name is Lyra Sycamore. If I had lived in a better world, none of you would ever find that out, and we'd all be happier for it. This world, though, doesn't allow for such luxuries. As it turns out, Neko already knew my real name anyways, so it was really only a matter of time before you all heard it. I guess I just wanted to tell you on my own terms. I guess I just wanted to have even the slightest bit of control over who I am.*
*The thing is, I've always had a complex about ambiguating my identity. Ever since I was a child, when I got forced out onto the streets, I didn't want anyone to know who I was. That's part of why I went through all those different names you've known me by- Nathan Strider, Arathorn Yodurou, Owen Stanford, Lumina Miyuz, more than I can remember... It's all rather obviously been for the sake of hiding who I was. Having all these different fake names was helpful as a cover.*
*At the same time, though, it was never just about that. Every time I went through these names, they really did mean something to me, I think. I didn't realize it until just recently, because I've always been able to explore this without much consequence, but it turns out that I care about being Horatius Kyodu as more than just a disguise. When I can't be that, it feels like something really important to me is being hurt. I've never felt this hurt before, and it feels strange, and scary, and most of all inescapable.*

*Up until now, I've gotten through my life by making compromises. No matter what happened to me, I'd always just not give a shit, tell myself to compromise, and move on. I was able to remain 'ambiguous' because nothing really mattered to me. Ironically, it was really easy to live like that, when I didn't value anything about my life. I didn't have to worry about any pain.*
*The further this revolution goes on, though, the more I realize that there's things that still matter. Every time someone calls me a girl, I feel so at odds with myself that I can't take it. Every time someone pulls back another layer of ambiguity, it feels like a knife cutting into my body. And the harder I fight, the more I'll have to do this, won't I?*
*I want to fight for the things that matter to me. I want to leave a mark on the world as the person who I truly feel comfortable being. But can I do that if my 'self' is rejected by that world? If my existence as myself is met with nothing but hatred, I can't be happy no matter what I do. And if I keep twisting myself into who the world wants me to be, making these compromises, am I really even myself anymore?*
*The more I do this, the less any of it makes sense to me. It just keeps getting harder and harder. I'm not strong enough to fight that. So I'm really sorry, but I'm giving up.*

*Wress, I'm especially sorry to you. Before all this happened, Neko told me you loved me, and I feel like a monster for killing the person you love. I just can't see you that way, though. I can't compromise myself into seeing you as a lover. I'm sorry I couldn't be that person for you.*
*Bern, this is much too late, but I've always loved you. You've been the kindest person I could have asked for throughout these past however many years, and it's your warmth that allowed me to stay alive for this long. You're one of the best people I've ever met, and I feel awful for only telling you that now. I guess this is one last bit of selfishness I'm allowing myself.*
*To the rest of the world, it would be better for all of us if you forgot I was ever here.*
